title: Cobb Salad with Green Goddess Dressing
summary: The recipe Cobb Salad with Green Goddess Dressing is ready in approximately 45 minutes and is definitely a spectacular gluten free option for lovers of American food. For $2.66 per serving, this recipe covers 28% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe makes 4 servings with 285 calories, 27g of protein, and 14g of fat each. Not a lot of people really liked this main course. 1 person found this recipe to be yummy and satisfying. If you have wine vinegar, flat-leaf parsley, pepper, and a few other ingredients on hand, you can make it. To use up the salt you could follow this main course with the Apple Turnovers Recipe as a dessert. With a spoonacular score of 69%, this dish is good. Try Cobb Salad with Green Goddess Dressing, Southwestern Cobb Salad with Green Goddess Dressing, and Green Goddess Cobb Salad for similar recipes.
instructions: To prepare dressing, place first 11 ingredients in a blender or food processor; process until smooth. Chill.                                                                                                To prepare salad, combine lettuce and watercress in a large bowl. Place 2 cups lettuce mixture on each of 4 plates. Arrange 6 tablespoons chicken, 4 tomato wedges, 2 egg wedges, 2 tablespoons avocado, and 1 tablespoon cheese over each serving. Serve each salad with 1/4 cup dressing.
